<points>


<li>
A blurred image has less abrupt areal changes than the original.
</li>

<li>
Thus, we can blur by averaging every pixel with some of the energy of its
neighbours.
</li>

<li>
A blurring acts as a low-pass filter by removing high areal frequencies
which cause abrupt changes.
</li>
</points>



